---
import { marked } from 'marked';
import leadRaw from '../markdown/in-the-box-lead.md?raw';

const leadHtml = marked.parse(leadRaw.trim(), { async: false });
---
<section class="in-the-box" aria-labelledby="h-box">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2 id="h-box">What’s in the box</h2>
    <div class="section-lead from-md" set:html={leadHtml} />
    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Rules</span>
        <h3>Project guardrails</h3>
        <p>
          Atlassian, browser (Charlotte/Playwright), token efficiency, data-eng workflows, and
          more — as <code>.mdc</code> files for Cursor rules.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Skills</span>
        <h3>Clarify, plan, present</h3>
        <p>
          Brainstorm, planning-brief, and presentation-creation (markdown → static HTML deck) with
          clear triggers in each <code>skills.md</code>.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Subagents</span>
        <h3>Single-role prompts</h3>
        <p>
          Implementer, tester, reviewer, and ship-writer: invoke one at a time or in sequence for
          a repeatable pipeline.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">MCP</span>
        <h3>Example servers</h3>
        <p>
          <code>mcp.json.example</code> +
          <a href="https://github.com/abhinavsinhanutan/Cursor-Workbench/blob/main/config/MCP.md"
            >MCP.md</a
          > describe code-review-graph, Charlotte, Playwright, and optional Tableau with
          placeholders only.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Hooks</span>
        <h3>Telemetry &amp; guard</h3>
        <p>
          Optional local JSONL logging and a Langfuse-oriented bundle with MCP write guard.
          Fail-open by design.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
